    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(center)"><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>!</p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Mobile</placeName>
                <date>August 27 1848</date>.</p>
            <p>Your favour from <date>17<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> inst., with
                acknowledgment<lb/> of the $20 00 in check on Pensilvan<add>?</add> Bank came
                to<lb/> Hand. I have according your Request, inquired of<lb/>
                <persName>Mr. Bowlumet<add>?</add></persName> in Reference to the Books you send
                in<lb/> his care for <persName>A Englander</persName>, he informs me that he
                    for<lb/><sic>wardet</sic> the same to a <persName>Mr Pfister</persName>
                Bookseller in <placeName>Montgome<lb/>ry</placeName> for deliverance, but as
                    <persName>Mr Englander</persName> has left since<lb/>
                <date>April</date> for <placeName>Germany</placeName> &amp; <persName>Mr
                    Englander</persName> is at present absent<lb/> from
                    <placeName>Montgomery</placeName>. I have instructed <persName>Mr H.
                    Lehman</persName> from<lb/>
                <persName>M.</persName> the Treasurer of the congregation to receive the Books<lb/>
                from <persName>Mr Pfister</persName> or to deliver the same to all who may<lb/> want
                any &amp; receive the money for the same. <persName>Mr De Silva</persName><lb/> says
                that he hath written to you about the Books &amp; <sic>sayd</sic><lb/> something
                about a Deduction on the same on account being<lb/> damaged. In Reference to those
                Gent: who are in arrears for<lb/> the <sic>occident</sic> I will exert myself to
                collect the money, but<lb/> I doubt if any will pay until they come here in Fall. I
                shall<lb/> nevertheless write to them about it. The are all good &amp; will<lb/> pay
                some Times.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I have sold &amp; engaged all the Prayerbooks but <del>as</del>
                I<lb/> have not rec. any payments, yet. I could sell probably several<lb/> copies
                more say 6 or 8 of those c $2 50. if I hath them<lb/> here. If you mind to send any
                you may do so, &amp; as <persName>Mr Y<lb/> Kayser</persName> probable sends out
                some <add>?</add> to me, you could<lb/> without</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>incurring any expenses send the along &amp; if you have any<lb/> Jewish calendars you
                will send me a few doz.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Mr I Newman</persName> &amp; <persName>P. Myers</persName>
                have recd the <sic>occident</sic> since<lb/> I wrote to you.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><sic>I</sic> conclusion, I remark that you owe me no thanks &amp;
                are under<lb/> no obligation to me whatever <del>?</del> for the little trouble<lb/>
                I have if any in gaining for you subscribers for the <sic>occident</sic><lb/> or in
                effecting some sales for your religious books. I am free<lb/> to confess, that,
                although I shall always feel happy to confer<lb/> a favour or serve in any manner my
                fellow Neighbour particular<lb/> a fellow believer, yet my prime object is in the
                above, to arouse<lb/> the <add>יהודים</add>
                <add>?</add> from that fatal indifference about their Religion<lb/> in which they
                are alas, so fearfully sunk &amp; this is the main<lb/> cause why I am so desirous
                of spreading among them some<lb/> good &amp; religious works like the
                    <sic>occident</sic>; but if in doing<lb/> so, I can or do serve you in any way I
                shall feel most happy<lb/> but as above stated the prime object is <del>in doing
                    so</del> a desire<lb/> of doing some good in <placeName>Israel</placeName>, or
                if I <sic>incidently</sic> serve you it<lb/> is not the primary object consequently
                you owe me nothing.<lb/> I desire no thanks &amp; neither Reward.</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">I am my dear sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">Yours very truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">
                <persName role="author">B M Emanuel</persName>
            </p>
            <p>P. S. If I can serve you</p>
            <p>in any thing or transaction which</p>
            <p>you may have here in the <placeName>south</placeName></p>
            <p>you are always welcome to write to me</p>
            <p>about it, I shall cheerfully attend to any thing</p>
            <p>you may require</p>
            <pb n="4"/>
            <p><addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee> Editor of</p>
            <p>Occident &amp; <sic>american</sic>
                <sic>jewish</sic> Advocate</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">
                <placeName>
                    <hi rend="underline">Philadelphia</hi>
                </placeName>
            </p>
